[node name="HelpDialog" type="AcceptDialog" parent="UI" unique_id=2005807090]
title = "How to Play Scoundrel"
size = Vector2i(480, 420)
dialog_text = "GOAL: Survive the dungeon. Start with 20 HP.

DECK: 44 cards (standard 52 minus red face cards & red aces).

EACH ROOM: 4 cards are dealt face-up. You MUST take at least 3.
Drag a card into a highlighted zone to take it:
  LEFT ZONE (green) — drink potions / equip weapons / fight with your weapon.
  RIGHT ZONE (blue) — discard potions or weapons / fight monsters bare-handed.
After 3 cards, 'Next Room' appears. The remaining card carries over.

MONSTERS (Clubs & Spades):
  2-10 = face value, J=11, Q=12, K=13, A=14.
  Drag LEFT (Fight w/ Weapon): damage = monster - weapon (min 0); weapon degrades.
  Drag RIGHT (Fight w/ Fists): take full damage, weapon floor is preserved.

WEAPONS (Diamonds, 2-10 only):
  Drag LEFT to equip. Replaces current weapon (old weapon discarded).
  Drag RIGHT to discard without equipping.
  Weapon value = card rank.

POTIONS (Hearts, 2-10 only):
  Drag LEFT to drink. Restore HP equal to rank, capped at 20.
  Drag RIGHT to discard without drinking.
  Only ONE potion heals per room (extras are wasted if drunk).

RUN: Skip an entire room — all 4 cards sink to the bottom of the deck.
  Monsters regroup (and take the loot with them). Cannot run two rooms in a row.

DEATH: Reach 0 HP.
WIN: Clear the deck"
